<HEADLINE> Uganda Commerce Officials Aim at Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda National Chamber of
Commerce and Industry has finalised arrangements for several
international business trips in a bid to secure international
business contacts for the prosperity of the country's business
sector.
</P>
<P>
According to Radio Uganda today, business trips to India,
Ethiopia, Rwanda and Zambia have been arranged for July.
</P>
<P>
In September, Uganda' enterpreneurs are scheduled to tour
Japan, Belgium, South Africa, Greece and the United Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Senegal are business destinations for the last
quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
The trips are aimed at enabling members of the chamber to
get experience from their counterparts so as to boost the
country's economy in a pace faster than before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
