<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Parliament Approves 1997/98 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian parliament, the
House of People's Representatives today approved over 10 billion
Birr (about 1.53 billion U.S Dollars) federal government budget for
the new fiscal year of 1997/98 beginning July 8, 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, about 3.7
billion Birr (about 544 million U.S. Dollars) was allocated for regular
budget, over 3.047 billion Birr (about 447 million U.S. Dollars) for
capital expenditure with the balance to go for subsidy to regions.
</P>
<P>
The report said, the annual national revenue is estimated at
over 8.4 billion Birr (about 1.23 billion U.S. Dollars) which
excels the income earned the previous fiscal year by 13.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's expenditure in 1996/97 was posted at 9.75 billion
Birr (about 1.43 billion U.S. Dollars). 
