<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Education Bill Stirs up Riots in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan riot police dispersed
stone-throwing university students on the streets near Nairobi
University this afternoon with at least one policemen seriously
injured.
</P>
<P>
Nairobi University students took to the streets to protest
against a proposed bill which proposes that college students who
fail to pay fees or any other levies be expelled from
universities.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 students threw stones at cars on the streets,
blocked rush-hour traffic for hours and destroyed some property.
</P>
<P>
Riot police used teargas and rubber bullets against rioting
students.
</P>
<P>
Students from the Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and
Technology yesterday blocked Thika Highway in Nairobi with stones
and burning tyres, protesting against the bill.
</P>
<P>
The students accused the Kenyan government of hatching a plot
to make education a preserve of the rich.
</P>
<P>
During the confrontation yesterday, two university students were
critically injured and some others arrested by Kenyan riot
police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
