<HEADLINE> U.S. Delivers Food to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. vessel has unloaded
17,000 tons of grain on the west coast of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK), and another ship carrying 8,000 tons of
grain is about to arrive in the city of Chongjin in northeastern
DPRK, State Department said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. deliveries are in response to an appeal last April for
emergency relief by the U.N. World Food Program, Spokesman
Nicholas Burns told reporters.
</P>
<P>
DPRK has allowed the World Food Program to send monitors to
ensure proper distribution of the food, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Rome-based World Food Program said on Thursday that it had
received almost all the 95.5 million US dollars it had requested
in its latest appeal to alleviate food shortage in DPRK, caused by
flooding which destroyed rice crops in 1995-96.
</P>
<P>
Burns also said that U.S. and DPRK officials met Wednesday
evening in New York to discuss a variety of issues, including the
preliminary peace talks set for next month involving DPRK, South
Korea, the United States and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
