<DOCNO> XIE19970704.0045 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornadoes Thunder Through Midwest of United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Governor John Engler of Michigan
in the United States has activated the National Guard and declared
a state of disaster in the Detroit area.
</P>
<P>
The governor is also asking the Federal Emergency Management
Agency (FEMA) to send a damage assessment team in hopes of
securing federal aid.
</P>
<P>
Engler made the announcement Thursday after touring devastated
areas, according to media reports.
</P>
<P>
These sections were among those hardest hit by a series of
tornadoes that ravaged five Michigan counties late Wednesday. The
storms killed at least eight, injuring more than 100 and leaving
hundreds homeless. Property damage is put at the tens of millions
of dollars.
</P>
<P>
Engler described the devastation as "beyond description."
</P>
<P>
The National Guard is being ordered to mobilize troops and
equipment to help with the cleanup and protect damaged buildings
from looters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
