<HEADLINE> Curfew Lifted in Cameroonian province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANUNDE, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The governor of Cameroon's Northwest
Province has lifted the dust to dawn curfew that was instituted in
the province since March 29, 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique issued by Governor Fai Yengo
Francis, the curfew was lifted on July 2, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Calm and security have progressively returned to the province.
</P>
<P>
The curfew was instituted after a group of armed individuals
attacked military and civilian constructions in six towns of
Northwest Province during which 13 people were killed.
</P>
</TEXT>
