<DOCNO> XIE19970704.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Auto Sales Keep Roaring Ahead in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Canadian auto sales posted a
fifth-straight month of double-digit growth in June, yet there
were signs the market may be cooling, said reports today.
</P>
<P>
Car and truck sales rose 11 percent last month, pushing vehicle
sales in Canada for the first half of the year to 697,546, the
highest level since the first six months of 1991.
</P>
<P>
"The momentum is there and we just don't see it going away," an
industry analyst was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Japan-based auto makers continued to lead the way in Canada for
most of the year and June was no exception.
</P>
<P>
Honda Canada Inc. of Toronto led the race with a 70 percent
jump to 10,446 car and truck sales, compared with 6,159 in June,
1996.
</P>
<P>
General Motors of Canada Ltd. sales were up 11.5 percent to
43,629, while sales at Ford Motor Co. of Canada Ltd. jumped 11.9
percent to 33,170, propelling the company to its best first half
since 1989.
</P>
<P>
Chrysler Canada Ltd. saw its June total fall 2.3 percent to
22,916 from the same month a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Among other automakers, Volvo Canada Ltd. had its best June in
23 years, selling 1,051 cars, a 1.5 percent boost from the
previous June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
