<HEADLINE> Novotna Injuried before Wimbledon Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Jana Novotna's hopes of winning
Wimbledon tennis women's singles title suffered a blow on
Friday when the Czech injured her thigh.
</P>
<P>
The third seed Novotna, due to meet top seed Martina Hingis in
Saturday's final, withdrew from Friday's doubles quarter-final due
to what the Women's Tennis Association (WTA) described as a
"chronic" thigh muscle problem.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the WTA put her playing ability at 75 percent
but said her chances of playing were "probable".
</P>
<P>
Novotna suffered the injury during a previous match and the
problem will be re-evaluated on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Novotna and American Lindsay Davenport, the third seeds in the
women's doubles, were due to play Sabine Appelmans of Belgium and
Miriam Oremans of the Netherlands in Friday's quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Czech has won 12 grand slam doubles titles,
including three women's doubles and one mixed doubles title at
Wimbledon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
