<HEADLINE> Japanese Buddhist Murdered in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese Buddhist was shot dead
Thursday night by a few masked men in the southern Nepali town of
Lumbini, the birthplace of Lord Buddha.
</P>
<P>
It is not known whether a Nepalese or any foreign group was
involved in the murder of Bhikshu Yunataka Nawatame, Nepali Deputy
Prime Minister and Home Minister Bamdev Gautam said in a statement
made at the Lower House today.
</P>
<P>
He said police had reached the site of the murder and arrested
eight suspects.
</P>
<P>
And a team has been sent to Lumbini to investigate the case, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Gautam strongly condemned the terrorist act, saying the
government will try to speedily find and take legal action against
the criminals. 
