<HEADLINE> World Climate Observing System China Committee Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The China Committee of the World
Climate Observing System was jointly set up today in Beijing by 13
departments, including the National Meteorological Bureau, the
State Bureau of Environment Protection, and the National Bureau of
Oceanography.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Song Jian welcomed the new committee,
calling on the members to increase cooperation, share
climate-related resources, and provide more efficient services for
sustained economic development.
</P>
<P>
The departments should work together to promote the application
of research achievements in atmosphere, oceanology, hydrology,
environment, and ecology, and develop international cooperation in
these fields, Song said.
</P>
<P>
The program for observing the world climate was initiated in
1992 by the World Meteorological Organization, UNESCO, the UN
Environment Program, and the World Federation of Scientific
Workers. 
</P>
