<HEADLINE> Riis' Bike Banned in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The 'special' bike which defending
champion Bjarne Riis of Denmark planned to ride in Saturday's Tour
de France opening race was banned by race organisers on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spanish rival Abraham Olano was also forbidden to use one of
the bikes provided by Italian maker Pinarello, as was Riis's
Deutsche Telekom teammate Jan Ullrich of Germany.
</P>
<P>
The ruling applied forbids "anything that reduces resistance
and offers artificial acceleration such as a fuselage".
</P>
<P>
Russian Pavel Tonkov suffered the same fate in the Giro
d'Italia last month.
</P>
<P>
Technical officials at the Union Cycliste International have
been tightening up on bike design.
</P>
<P>
Track bikes used to win Olympic golds in Atlanta have since
been outlawed by new rulings on their dimensions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
