<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech Urging People to Press Forward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
speech that reveals the light shed by the modern history on the
Chinese nation has inspired deep thought in the people and urged
them to press forward.
</P>
<P>
This is the general opinion expressed by experts,
scholars and ordinary people alike after hearing the speech
delivered by the Chinese present at Beijing's mass rally to
celebrate Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang said that the modern history of China
makes clear the truth that the Chinese nation must rise in
struggle and work hard to make the country strong if it is to
change the historical fate of being bullied and oppressed due to
poverty and backwardness; that it must have the leadership of an
advanced political Party and the guidance of a scientific theory
if it is to realize national liberation and prosperity and
strength of the country; and that it must break away with the
state of being closed and must open up the country to the rest of
the world if it is to catch up with the progress of the times and
the development trend of the world..
</P>
<P>
Su Junhong, a researcher from Kunming, capital city of Yunnan
Province in the southwest, said the president's speech is
penetrating. The return of Hong Kong is the result of the growing
strength of the Chinese nation, which is in turn the result of the
growing strength of the leadership of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) and the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Staff members from the library of Nanjing University said that
Jiang's speech has filled them with confidence in the long-term
stability of Hong Kong, in the leadership of the CPC, in the
realization of the targets set by Deng Xiaoping for building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and in the ultimate
settlement of the Taiwan issue based on the principle of "one
country, two systems."  
</P>
</TEXT>
