<HEADLINE> Senior Party Official Urges to Strengthen Party Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A senior Communist Party of China
(CPC) official has urged continued efforts to do research in Party
building and promote the Party building work in an all-round
manner.
</P>
<P>
The call came from Hu Jintao, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, in
an article congratulating on the publication of the 100th issue
of the magazine "Party Building Research".
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed out that China has now entered an important period
of development, and the entire Party and Chinese nation should
work to bring into the 21st century the cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics, initiated by late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that Party building in an all-round manner is a great
project which has been very fruitful over the past few years. But
he said that there are still some new problems that need urgent
solution.
</P>
<P>
In building the Party under the new situation, he said, the
most important thing is to equip the Party with Marxism-Leninism
and Mao Zedong Thought and the theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics advanced by Deng Xiaoping so as to enhance
the ideological and political qualities of Party members, such as
persistence in serving the people wholeheartedly, maintaining
blood-and-flesh relations with the people and raising the ability
of resisting corrosion by decadent ideas.
</P>
<P>
He called for great efforts to improve democratic centralism,
strengthen grassroots organizations and select outstanding
young cadres.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the problems existing in the Party in the
areas of ideology, organization and style of work should be
studied in the context of deepening reform, promoting development
and maintaining stability and should solved by employing scientific
theories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
