<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine policemen today killed
two drug traffickers and arrested 31 other members of a drug
syndicate in an intensified anti-drug campaign launched in Metro
Manila.
</P>
<P>
The policemen raided several hideouts of the notorious drug
ring in Quezon city, party of Metro Manila. The head of the
syndicate resisted arrest and was killed in a shoot-out. Another
member of the gang was also killed.
</P>
<P>
Among the things confiscated from the hideouts include
kilograms of shabu, a popular kind of drug in the Philippines,
several high-power firearms and a certain amount of bullets,
police said.  
