<HEADLINE> Indonesians Urged to Patronize Domestic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto today
called on the people to get used to patronizing Indonesian
products in anticipation of global free trade.
</P>
<P>
"If people prefer to patronize foreign products, there will be
no market for domestic products," the president said when
receiving local officials at the Merdeka Palace here.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Indonesian nation must be accustomed to using
domestic products from now on because by the year 2020, trade will
be liberalized in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
He said developed countries can produce better and cheaper
products than Indonesia because they have mastered science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
To prevent domestic industries from going bankrupt, children
who will experience the impact of liberalized trade by 2020 must
be accustomed to using domestic products from now on, he said.
</P>
