<HEADLINE> State Councillors Meet Tightrope Walker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- State councillors Li Tieying and
Ismayil Aymat today met Adili, a tightrope walker from China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, who on June 22 fulfilled his
long-time dream of walking the high wire across the Yangtze River,
China's longest, in 13 minutes 48 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Adili's feat of derring-do broke the existing Guinness World
Record set in 1995 by Canadian Jay Cochraine, who crossed the
river in 53 minutes 10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
As a seventh-generation member of the Dawazi family, famed
professional tightrope walkers from Xinjiang, Adili tread across a
640.75-meter steel wire stretching 375 meters above the Yangtze
River over the Qutang Gorge, one of the well-known Three Gorges.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying congratulated Adili on his daring feat, saying that
it reveals China's courageous spirit to the world. Ismayil Aymat
said that Adili's success embodies the sense of solidarity among
different ethnic groups. 
</P>
