<HEADLINE> Germany Quickens Deportation Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A draft law was approved in Germany
today in a bid to free up the deportation of foreigners committing
criminal offences in the country.
</P>
<P>
The bill, approved Friday by the upper house of parliament and
earlier by the lower house, mainly targets drug traffickers and
foreign demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, Germany authorities will automatically start
deportation proceedings against any foreigner sentenced to more
than three years in jail, or those convicted of a serious case of
breaching public security regardless of the jail terms.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners using violence during illegal or dispersed
demonstrations could also face deportation without trial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
