<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and two
injured today in a landslide resulting from a three-hour-long
pouring rain along the Black Sea in Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
