<HEADLINE> Killing of Newspaper Columnist Solved in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine police announced today
the solution of a case in which a famous columnist of a Manila
tabloid was shot to death in a taxi earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Efren Fernandez, director of the Philippine National Police
Criminal Investigation Group, said the cracking of the case came
after the arrest of a former auto painter and a member of a
notorious gang, who preyed on unwary taxi passengers in the past
few years in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
However, friends and families believed that Danilo Hernandez,
47, a columnist of People's Tonight, was killed by a drug
syndicate on June 2 for his vehement attack on drug traffickers in
his articles.
</P>
<P>
The auto painter, arrested after a gunfight on July 2, has
admitted participation in the killing of Hernandez. He pointed to
the gang member as the gunman who shot Hernandez in the head,
Fernandez said.
</P>
<P>
Hernandez's death hit the headlines. At a press conference held
in the Presidential Palace, President Fidel Ramos urged the
immediate arrest of the murderers.  
