<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Telecom System Adopted For Flood Control Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China has invested 58 million
yuan in a new telecommunications system to ensure efficient
information flow for flood control efforts in the lower reaches of
the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
Work on the microwave telecommunications system, which includes
44 program-controlled telephone exchanges and six one-point
multiple-address microwave central stations, started in March this
year.
</P>
<P>
All the hydrological stations and river administrative bureaus
and sluice-gate control centers have realized wireless and
program-controlled telecommunications. The facilities have also
provided reliable channels for computer networking and data
transmission. 
</P>
