<HEADLINE> Turkey Asks for Help to Put Out Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has asked foreign countries
for help to put out a strong fire in a state-owned munition
factory in central Turkey Thursday, a Turkish official statement
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry statement said that Turkey asked Israel,
France, Britain, the United States and the Netherlands to
provide assistance for extinguishing the raging fire which
engulfed the TNT ammunition manufacturing complex owned by the
Machinery and Chemical Industry (MKE) company in the city of
Kirikkale.
</P>
<P>
Two Israeli helicopters and one transport plane carrying
technical equipment and 41 crew arrived at Akincilar Air Base
today and the two helicopters took part in the fight against the
flames from the air at 11:00 local time (08:00 GMT), said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said that France promised to dispatch
three fire experts to Turkey this noon, and Britain and the
U.S. will provide all kinds of logistic support in a bid to
put out the fire.
</P>
<P>
The explosions rocked the ammunitions factory in Kirikkale,
killing two people and injuring many others including three
policemen.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of civilians were evacuated from the
neighborhood as a precautionary step.
</P>
<P>
Turkish President Suleymand Demirel and other leaders rushed
to the city Thursday evening to inspect the explosion site and
battle against the fire.
</P>
<P>
Turkish daily newspaper "Zaman" reported today that in the
previous explosion of the ammunition factory in Kirikkale in 1986,
11 people were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
