<HEADLINE> Shenzhen, HK Make New Progress in Financial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen plans to take advantage
of Hong Kong's homecoming to step up cooperation with Hong Kong in
the financial sector, so as to open Shenzhen's banking industry
wider to the rest of the world, the director of the Shenzhen
Branch of the People's Bank of China said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a gathering of local bankers in south China's
Shenzhen, Jiang Chaoliang said everything is ready to start
exchange of bills between Shenzhen and Hong Kong and the payment
and settlement systems of the two places are expected to be linked
up soon.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shenzhen is also trying to win approval from the
central authorities for setting up joint venture security
companies, cooperative funds and joint venture insurance firms in
Shenzhen and for allowing Shenzhen-based overseas banks to handle
Renminbi yuan business, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen's financial industry has been brisk since the
beginning of this year. Banks have provided 53 billion yuan in
loans and the amount of financing through money markets came to
nearly 100 billion yuan of funds raised from the local financial
market since the beginning of this year. The amount of loans
provided by Shenzhen-based foreign banks increased by 10.8
percent. 
</P>
