<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to strong showing of
electronics and components exports, the Philippines' exports rose
to 9.6 billion U.S. dollars in the first five months of this year,
a 22.7 percent increase over a year earlier, the National
Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
Exports for May alone increased by 22.2 percent to reach nearly
2 billion U.S. dollars, compared to 1.6 billion dollars a year
ago.
</P>
<P>
In May, electronics and components continued to be the
country's top foreign reserve earner, with earnings from them
reaching 881 million dollars and accounting for 44.8 percent of
the total export revenue for the month.
</P>
<P>
The second biggest earner for the month was articles of apparel
and clothing accessories, which had a combined income of 189
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The United States continued to be the country's biggest market,
which imported 672 million worth of goods from the Philippines. It
was followed by Japan, the Netherlands and Singapore.  
</P>
