Kaohsiung, Taipei, Qingdao, Xiamen, Wuhan and Bangkok, Air Macao
reported a business performance much better than expected after it
received the millionth passenger in May.
</P>
<P>
It now has a fleet of six planes, including four Airbus A-321s
and two Airbus A-320s. The air company started its commercial
operation in November 1995 following the inauguration of the Macao
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Macao International Airport handled a total of
962,900 passengers in the first half of the year, which is almost
twice the number it handled in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The airport also reported a sharp increase in cargo
transport. It handled 18,000 tons of goods in the first six months
of the year, three times the amount it handled in the same period
last year. 
