<HEADLINE> Yeltsin: Military Reform Priority of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia's first priority in 1997 is
to carry out a military reform, Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said in a regular broadcast to the nation today.
</P>
<P>
In his address, Yeltsin said the Russian army should become
mobile, well organized, equipped with high-accuracy weapons and
smaller in size.
</P>
<P>
