<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto to Open Asia-Europe Business Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- President Soeharto will open the
Asia-Europe Business Conference to be held here from July 8 to 10,
Chairman of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry
Aburizal Bakrie said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing here, Bakrie said about 350
participants from the European Union and Asian countries would
attend the meeting organized by the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce
and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Asia will represented by China, Japan, South Korea, as well as
member countries of the ASEAN, namely Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia,
the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The conference is a follow-up activity of the decision of the
inaugural summit of Asia-Europe meeting in Bangkok in March 1996
and taking into account the recommendations of the first business
forum in Paris in October last year, Bakrie said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, some ministers from Indonesia and leading
businessmen are expected to make speeches and submit their papers
on economic cooperation between the two regions, he said.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the conference, is to disseminate and
exchange information and experiences on economic, trade and
investment policies, business environment and practices by the two
regions, officials here said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will provide a comprehensive perspective on the
economic and business opportunities in both regions, particularly
in trade and investment, as a basis for future cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It will also promote dialogue and establish network among the
private sector and business communities of Asia and Europe,
including small and medium size enterprises, Bakrie said.
</P>
<P>
The result of the meeting will be reported to the economic
ministers meeting to be held in November this year in Bangkok, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Based on the spirit of the first Asia-Europe summit meeting and
the above mentioned objectives, he said, the theme for the
business conference is "strengthening the dynamic synergy and
partnership of Asia-Europe business interactions."  
</P>
