<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Lower on Rate Sentiment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly lower against its US counterpart today with the market
caught up in sentiment that a cut to domestic interest rates is
still possible.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 75.23 US cents, down from 75.30
US cents in Sydney late Thursday after trading in a tight range of
75.15 US cents to 75.27 US cents.
</P>
<P>
Macquarie Bank's Foreign Exchange Manager Mark O'Leary said the
Australian dollar had sold off overnight after the Reserve Bank of
Australian (RBA) announced that it had completed a six-month
program to sell 167 tons of gold bullion, cutting its reserves by
two thirds.
</P>
<P>
Locally today gold bullion closed at 323.75 US dollars an ounce
from 332.60 at its close Thursday.
</P>
<P>
O'Leary said buyers in the market had helped keep the
Australian dollar above the 0.7500 US dollar level today.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed in Sydney at 85.26 Japanese yen,
down from 86.13 yen and at 1.3167 German marks down from 1.3102
marks.  
</P>
