<HEADLINE> Southwest China Port Attracts Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Beihai port in the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, southwest China, has been successful in
attracting overseas investment since it gained the status of an
open coastal city in 1984.
</P>
<P>
For nearly 13 years, overseas investment in the city has
accounted for 40.47 percent of its total. It attracted 66.77
percent of the total Hong Kong investment in Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Beihai had 886 Hong Kong-backed
projects, involving a contractual total of three billion US
dollars. Hong Kong's investment covers real estate, construction,
industrial development, communications, tourism, food service, and
entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Beihai was one of 14 coastal cities which began to open up
to overseas business in 1984. 
</P>
