<HEADLINE> China to Join International Accounting Standards Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China will formally join the
International Accounting Standards Committee (IASC) next week,
when the committee holds a meeting in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
This announcement was made by Michael Sharp, chairman of IASC,
at a meeting in Shanghai. He says that because of the Chinese
economy's immense potential for the next century, it is very
important for China to become a member of IASC, which has 120
accounting organizations in 90 countries.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred officials and experts from the famous
international Coopers &AMP; Lybrand, Chinese Ministry of Finance, the
China Securities Regulatory Commission, Chartered Bank, CitiBank,
the Shanghai International Trust and Investment Corporation, the
New York Stock Exchange, and some other companies attended the
meeting. 
</P>
