<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Wuyi Mountain, a major scenic area
in Fujian Province in southeast China, had 550,000 tourists in the
first five months of this year, up 33 percent from the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Included in this number were 42,000 overseas tourists, a rise
of 62 percent, statistics from the local tourism bureau show.
</P>
<P>
A number of gardens have been built in the mountain area,
bringing the afforestation rate there to 82 percent, from 28
percent in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The local government has spent more than 50 million yuan on
restoration work on a number of ancient buildings and for new
tourist routes in the past few years.  
</P>
