<HEADLINE> British set to ban Tyson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson might never have a chance
to fight in Britain as The British Boxing Board of Control (BBBC)
meets next week to decide whether to ban the American boxer
following his ear-biting assault on Evander Holyfield.
</P>
<P>
And any British boxer who fights Mike Tyson in the future faces
having his licence revoked.
</P>
<P>
BBBC chairman Leonard Read is recommending the ban and wants
stiffer measures included to stop British fighters taking on the
former world heavyweight champion in any match held abroad.
</P>
<P>
Read, who described Tyson's attack as "cannibalistic", will
also write to the European Boxing Union asking them to extend any
ban to the whole of Europe.
</P>
<P>
The BBBC have already written to the Nevada State Athletic
Commission recommending a life ban when they meet to decide the
fighter's punishment on Wednesday. 
