-- Nigeria and six other west African countries have closed
down their embassies in Freetown, Sierra Leone, following the
directive of the Committee of Foreign Ministers in the ECOWAS
sub-region.
</P>
<P>
Vanguard
</P>
<P>
-- Former U.S. president, Jimmy Carter who met with Nigeria's
head of state General Sani Abacha in Abuja recently, believed the
campaign that Abacha should succeed himself is not quite popular,
even within the military. 
