<DOCNO> XIE19970704.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Official Briefs On Public Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A principal official of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region said here today that there
would be continuity in the policy of managing public finance.
</P>
<P>
Kwong Ki Chi, secretary for the treasury of the Hong Kong SAR
said at a media briefing: "I'm so confident about it because all
the policies have, in fact, been enshrined in the Basic Law."
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law provides that the Hong Kong SAR shall have
independent finances and practise an independent taxation system.
</P>
<P>
In Article 107, the mini constitution of the Hong Kong SAR
stipulates that the HKSAR shall follow the principle of keeping
expenditure within the limits of revenues in drawing up its
budget, and strive to achieve a fiscal balance, avoid deficits and
keep the budget commensurate with the growth rate of its gross
domestic product.
</P>
<P>
He noted that "the underlying philosophy guiding the
management of public finance in Hong Kong is to keep a small
government and live within our means."
</P>
<P>
"We do believe that small is beautiful. The main reason is that
we firmly believe that private sector is the engine of growth and
the government should not consume so much resources of the
community to squeeze out the private sector," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the secretary for treasury, the Hong Kong SAR will
continue to take strict control of the government expenditure so
as to achieve the goal of living within one's means.
</P>
<P>
The growth of the government expenditure should follow the
trend growth rate of the economy, and the GDP growth is based on a
five-year planning period, said Kwong. As to the revenue policy,
he added, a low, simple and predictable taxation system would
remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Kwong estimated that the financial reserves on March 13, 1998,
the end of this financial year would stand at about 48 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
