<HEADLINE> Memorial Hall for Resistance War Against Japanese Aggression </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Second-phase construction work at
the memorial hall commemorating China's war of resistance against
Japanese aggression has been completed in the southwest of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The memorial hall, which also functions as a museum, will stage
new exhibitions to mark the 60th anniversary of the "July 7
Incident" in 1937, also called the Marco Polo Bridge incident,
which preluded Japan's attempted full-scale invasion of China.
</P>
<P>
Located beside the Marco Polo Bridge, the second-phase project
of the hall consists of an extension to the main hall and a data
center on China's war of resistance against Japanese
aggression. It covers a total of 10,300 square meters.
</P>
