<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Former President to Appear in Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's former President Canaan
Banana will soon be charged with 11 counts involving sodomy,
attempted sodomy and indecent assault, Attorney-General Patrick
Chinamasa has said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement available today, Chinamasa said that Banana
would be indicted within the next few days.
</P>
<P>
''My office has studied the police crime docket submitted to
me this week. On the facts as disclosed, i am satisfied that
reverend Canaan Sodindo Banana, the former state president, has a
case to answer,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
''Accordingly, i have directed that he be prosecuted before a
judge of the high court,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Banana will face two counts of sodomy relating to charges
filed by his former aide-de-camp Jefta Dube. He will also face
two counts of attempted sodomy.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he faces seven counts of indecent assault in
relation to complaints filed by six aides-de-camp and a gardener
from Harare.
</P>
<P>
Chinamasa said, ''the trial will be held in open court, but
for the protection of witnesses' reputations, their names and
particulars of their identities may not be made public. at the
trial, an order to this effect will be sought.'' 
