<HEADLINE> Trade Between S. Africa, Pakistan Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Trade between South Africa
and Pakistan has increased from 63 million Rand (14 million U.S.
Dollars) to 600 million Rand (133 million Dollars) between 1993
and this year, local daily "Business Report" said today.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral trade focused primarily on a narrow range of
traditional exports and imports, Anneesuddin Ahmed, High
Commissioner for Pakistan was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's exports to Pakistan were dominated by base
metals, downstream petro-chemicals products and textiles, while
imports from Pakistan were dominated by textiles, leather goods,
carpets and sporting goods, Ahmed said.
</P>
<P>
