<HEADLINE> All-Stars Soccer Match Marks HK's Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- An International Football
Federation (FIFA) All-Stars team scored a spectacle 5-3 win over
an Asian Football Confederation (AFC) All-Stars side in an
international soccer match here Thursday evening to mark Hong
Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Although the organizers had difficulties getting all the
players they had wished to invite to the match, the spectators
enjoyed a match which could be taken as of the world-class
caliber in the Hong Kong Stadium.
</P>
<P>
The AFC All-Stars team opened the score when Iranian Khodadad
Azizi found the net 16 minutes into the game.
</P>
<P>
But the more skillful players of the FIFA All-Stars side
demonstrated their capability despite of the fact they had little
time to train together before the match.
</P>
<P>
Liberia's FIFA Footballer of the Year George Weah levelled the
score at the 18th minute when he drizzled the ball to the edge of
the goal zone and launched a tricky shot.
</P>
<P>
It was followed by goals by Spanish Miguel Alfonso at the 25th
minute and by Turkey's Hakan Sukur at the 32nd minute.
</P>
<P>
The two teams each put in two more goals in the second half,
which paved way for a 5-3 victory for the FIFA All-Stars team.
</P>
<P>
Scorers:
</P>
<P>
For FIFA All-Stars: George Weah (18th minute), Miguel Alfonso
(25th), Hakan Sukur (32nd), Claudio Reyna (53rd) and Jean-Pierre
Papin (68th);
</P>
<P>
For AFC All-Stars: Khodadad Azizi (16th), Moahmmed Salem Al
Enazi (74th) and Karim Bagheri Korogh (79th).
