<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Customs Handling Procedures Faster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Wusong Customhouse has
made it more convenient for a number of large and medium-sized
enterprises to clear customs faster than ever.
</P>
<P>
Beginning this month, enterprises that have a good record can
report imports at an "Express Window" so that the cargo is
released immediately upon arrival, with customs duties collected
later.
</P>
<P>
The Wusong customhouse is the largest in Shanghai and handles
about 80 percent of the city's imports and exports.
</P>
<P>
The "Express Window" will greatly facilitate the importing of
raw materials and equipment and will increase competitiveness in
the marketplace, authorities say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
