<HEADLINE> Chinese Island Province To Join Island Tour Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- South China's island province of
Hainan is set to join island tour organization in Southeast Asia
to develop tourism and unify the market for greater efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
have been discussing establishing an island tour community for
Southeast Asia, and want Sanya City on the southern tip of Hainan
to be included. Meanwhile, the Republic of Korea's Cheju Province
also plans to join Japan's Okinawa, Indonesia's Bali, and Hainan
in a similar arrangement.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that Hainan plans to attend a ceremony
marking the establishment of an "Island Tour Policy Forum", which
will be held in Cheju this month.
</P>
<P>
Hainan, with its good environment and tropical tourism
resources, is considered a competitive tourist destination for the
international market. It was awarded a "New Tourism Destination
with Great Prospects" award at an international tourism fair held
in Hong Kong last year.
</P>
<P>
The province has two international airports, more than 300
hotels and holiday villages, and regular air service or chartered
air service to Hong Kong, Macao, Thailand, Singapore, Malaysia,
Japan, and the ROK. It receives more than 300,000 overseas
tourists each year. 
</P>
