<HEADLINE> 26 Tamil Rebel Suspects Arrested in South Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police Thursday night
arrested 26 Tamil rebel suspects including two women in Ratmalana
Town, about 20 kilometers from Colombo, according to police
sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The suspects who had tried to pose as estate Tamils had
actually arrived from the North.
</P>
<P>
They are now being interrogated by a special police team, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Police believed that they are a team of Tamil rebel cadres sent
to Colombo to attack VIPs and important installations in the
Capital city.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 14-year war against the
government for a separate state in the North and East of the
country during which over 55,000 persons have died.  
</P>
</TEXT>
