<HEADLINE> China to Establish Forest Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A forest museum will be set up in
the Chinese capital for scientific, educational, and tourism
purposes.
</P>
<P>
The museum will be located in the Jiulongshan mountains in the
western suburbs of Beijing, 24 kms from the downtown area.
</P>
<P>
With more than 50 types of vegetation and nearly a hundred
kinds of animals, the location provides good natural environmental
conditions.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to be built in eight years. Preparatory work
backed by the Forestry Ministry is underway.  
</P>
