<HEADLINE> L. American Coffee Producers to Set up Organization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Latin American coffee
producers plan to deepen regional integration by forming an
organization to improve technology exchange, the Brazilian press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A proposal to set up the Organization of Latin American and
Caribbean coffee Producers' Cooperatives will be approved at the
next meeting of the region's coffee producers, the president of
the Brazilian cooperatives was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Latin American countries account for 60 percent of world coffee
production, with Brazil, the biggest producer, supplying 28
percent. Latin America is the main producer of Arabica coffee, the
most sought after and most expensive one in the international
market. 
