<HEADLINE> Brazil Issues Second Lire-denominated Eurobonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Spurred by the success of
its June eurobond issue in Italy, the Brazilian government on
Wednesday launched its second lire-denominated issue on the
Italian market on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 250 million-lire (146.3 million U.S. dollars) issue carries
a 10.95 percent annual interest rate, five basis points higher
than June's 500 million-lire (441 million dollars) bond issue, and
matures on June 27, 2017, said Marcio Cartier, consultant to the
Central Bank's Foreign Affairs section. 
</P>
