<HEADLINE> Uruguay To Host Basketball Americas Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Montevideo of Uruguay will host
the Americas men's basketball championship slated from August 21
to 31.
</P>
<P>
The 10 Americas teams will take part in the 10-day event are
Canada, the United States, Cuba, Mexico, Puerto Rico, Dominican
Republic, Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay, and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will start with two groups of five-team each in
the first round and the top four finishers in each group qualify
for the second round.
</P>
<P>
The eight-team round-robin second phase will decide the top
four finisher who qualifying for the 1998 Greece world men's
basketball championship.
</P>
<P>
The United States, the defending world champion, is
automatically enter the 16-team 1998 world championship with host
Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
