<HEADLINE> Venezuela, Colombian Presidents to Meet in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan and Colombian
presidents will meet in the first week of August in the Colombian
border city of Cucuta.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to focus on the border issue, security,
infrastructure works, economic and social development, bilateral
trade and the stolen vehicles problem.
</P>
<P>
Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera and his Colombian
counterpart, Ernesto Samper, will also inaugurate the new
Venezuelan consulate in Cucuta.
</P>
<P>
The foreign and defense ministers of the two countries will
also take part in the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
