<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 19 Killed, 12 Injured in Spanish Shipyard Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 19 people were killed and
12 others injured in an explosion on a cargo ship under
construction in the Spanish port city of Valencia on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All the victims were workers on the ship, which caught fire
after a fuel leak on board triggered an explosion just after
midday (1000 GMT), a port official said.
</P>
<P>
The workers who died were trapped inside the boat's engine room
after the explosion at the Naval de Levante union shipyard. A
spokesman for the shipbuilders said many of the victims died as a
result of suffocation and smoke inhalation.
</P>
<P>
The 110-meter-long ship, named "Proof Spirit", was being built
for a Norwegian company to carry chemicals. It was expected to be
finished by September, but has been completely destroyed by the
fire.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major ship fire in Spain since May 1985 when
two oil tankers exploded killing 21. The Valencia government has
promised a full investigation into the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
