<HEADLINE> Mercosur Mining Summit to Be Held in Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The first Mercosur mining summit
will be held in Uruguay in November to discuss common problems and
the progress achieved in the sector by the four member states of
the South American trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
By that time, work to systemize mining legislation in the four
countries will be completed, Gonzalo Ilarramendi, director of
Mining and Geology at the Uruguayan Industry, Energy and Mining
Ministry, said today.
</P>
<P>
Legislators, officials, entrepreneurs and relevant
organizations from Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay will
take part in the summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
