<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Virginia Highway Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were
killed in a multivehicle accident that occurred Thursday afternoon
on Interstate 95 near Emporia, Virginia, in the United States.
</P>
<P>
A spokesperson for the Virginia State Police in Emporia, told
United Press International that traffic was shut down for several
hours in the southbound direction and remained blocked at 7 p.m.
in the northbound lanes.
</P>
<P>
The accident involved at least four or five vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Emporia is located about 65 miles south of the state capital of
Richmond and just 10 miles north of the North Carolina
border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
