<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Financing for Three Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of the financing totaling some 105 million U.S.
dollars for projects in three countries.
</P>
<P>
First credit of about 41.3 million dollars equivalent will be
provided for the second national agricultural services development
project in Burkina Faso, West Africa. The project will finance
training for farmers, particularly women, and farming advisors, in
crop production and animal husbandry as well as a program to
strengthen farmer organizations.
</P>
<P>
A loan of some 42.5 million dollars will help Indonesia's safe
motherhood project. This project will finance information,
education and communication activities to improve reproductive
health, and training, medical equipment, surveys and research to
improve maternal health services in the Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of some 16.7 million dollars equivalent is
earmarked for Mongolia's Ulaanbaatar services improvement project.
This project will finance construction of pipelines, reservoirs,
and other plumbing infrastructure to strengthen water supply
services and training for the water and sanitation company of
Ulaanbaatar.
</P>
<P>
The two credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending wing of
the World Bank for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
